In all cypriniform fishes, excluding members of the Gyrinocheilidae , pharyngobranchial 1 is absent ( Figs 11 , 32 , 33C–I ). Members of the Catostomidae possess only its cartilaginous precursor, pharyngobranchial-1 cartilage ( Siebert, 1987 ;
Engeman et al . 2009
; Fig. 33A ). In members of the Gyrinocheilidae and in all outgroup taxa, pharyngobranchial 1 is present ( Fig. 33B ).

